{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.5",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 5 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:1",
      "text": "“Call now; is there any who will answer you? To which of the holy ones will you turn?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:2",
      "text": "For resentment kills the foolish man, and jealousy kills the simple.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:3",
      "text": "I have seen the foolish taking root, but suddenly I cursed his habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:4",
      "text": "His children are far from safety. They are crushed in the gate. Neither is there any to deliver them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:5",
      "text": "whose harvest the hungry eat up, and take it even out of the thorns. The snare gapes for their substance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:6",
      "text": "For affliction doesn’t come out of the dust, neither does trouble spring out of the ground;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:7",
      "text": "but man is born to trouble, as the sparks fly upward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:8",
      "text": "“But as for me, I would seek God. I would commit my cause to God,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:9",
      "text": "who does great things that can’t be fathomed, marvelous things without number;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:10",
      "text": "who gives rain on the earth, and sends waters on the fields;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:11",
      "text": "so that he sets up on high those who are low, those who mourn are exalted to safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:12",
      "text": "He frustrates the plans of the crafty, so that their hands can’t perform their enterprise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:13",
      "text": "He takes the wise in their own craftiness; the counsel of the cunning is carried headlong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:14",
      "text": "They meet with darkness in the day time, and grope at noonday as in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:15",
      "text": "But he saves from the sword of their mouth, even the needy from the hand of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:16",
      "text": "So the poor has hope, and injustice shuts her mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:17",
      "text": "“Behold, happy is the man whom God corrects. Therefore do not despise the chastening of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:18",
      "text": "For he wounds and binds up. He injures and his hands make whole.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:19",
      "text": "He will deliver you in six troubles; yes, in seven no evil will touch you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:20",
      "text": "In famine he will redeem you from death; in war, from the power of the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:21",
      "text": "You will be hidden from the scourge of the tongue, neither will you be afraid of destruction when it comes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:22",
      "text": "You will laugh at destruction and famine, neither will you be afraid of the animals of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:23",
      "text": "For you will be allied with the stones of the field. The animals of the field will be at peace with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:24",
      "text": "You will know that your tent is in peace. You will visit your fold, and will miss nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:25",
      "text": "You will know also that your offspring will be great, your offspring as the grass of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:26",
      "text": "You will come to your grave in a full age, like a shock of grain comes in its season.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.5.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:27",
      "text": "Behold, we have researched it. It is so. Hear it, and know it for your good.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
